Express Js Middleware
-middleware are functions that have access to the request object(req), the presponce(res), and the next middleware functions in the application's request-respoxe cycle.
-used to modify req and res objects for task
syntax :
    app.use(function(req, res, next){
        //codes
        next();
    });


    day 4
order of middlware calls
- In Express middleware functions execute in order in which they are written/included in file



third party middleware

body parser 
- it is used to parse the body of requests,
- to use body parser we need to install using:
    npm install --save body-parser
-and we need to require to use it:
    var bodyParser = require('body-parser');

cookie parser
-It is used to parse Cookie header and populate req.cookies with an object keyed by cookie names
- to use body parser we need to install using:
    npm install --save cookie-parser
and then require it:
    var cookieParser = require('cookie-parser');
and then use it
    var cookieParser = require('cookie-parser');
    app.use(cookieParser())


express-session
It creates a session middleware with the given options. We will discuss its usage in the Sessions section.